Package: securer
Title: Secure R Code Execution with Tool-Call IPC
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ian", "Flores Siaca", email = "iflores.siaca@hey.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Wraps callr::r_session with a bidirectional IPC protocol for
    pause/resume tool calls, enabling safe execution of LLM-generated R code.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://ian-flores.github.io/securer/,
    https://github.com/ian-flores/securer
BugReports: https://github.com/ian-flores/securer/issues
SystemRequirements: bubblewrap (bwrap, Linux, optional), sandbox-exec
    (macOS, included with OS, optional), PowerShell (Windows, included with
    OS, optional)
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Imports:
    callr (>= 3.7.0),
    processx (>= 3.8.0),
    R6,
    jsonlite
Suggests:
    covr,
    ellmer (>= 0.3.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
